    "body": "Hey @eu09,\r\nThe real issue with enabling a gas-fee on an IBFT2 network, is the _creation_ and distribution of Eth, such that users of the network can apply a non-zero gas price to their transactions.\r\n\r\nSo, all accounts can be given an allocation up front via the genesis file, but, how do you \"top them up\" over time?\r\nThe answer is to enable mining rewards in the network such that a specific account will be paid a fixed sum per block (along with transaction fees).\r\nThe maintainer of this account is then responsible for distributing this generated Eth to all users of the network in whatever way they see fit - i.e. this account becomes the \"central bank\" of the network.\r\n\r\nTo enable mining rewards you need to add:\r\n* miningbeneficiary (hex address), and\r\n* blockreward (in wei)\r\nto your genesis file (on all nodes - i.e. everyone must agree that someone will get paid, or else blocks will be invalid).\r\n\r\nThen, when starting your validators, add the min-gas-price to set an appropriate gas-price for the network (i.e. a non-zero value) - this then will ensure that all nodes must supply an acceptable gasPrice to their transactions for their transactions to be mined, and therefore pay the subsequent Eth.\r\n",
